<subSubSection pageId="198" pageNumber="477" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="198.[2060,2654,3058,3480]" pageId="198" pageNumber="477">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[2061,2217,3058,3087]" pageId="198" pageNumber="477">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Myers &amp; Patton, 1989" authorityName="Myers &amp; Patton" authorityYear="1989" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Akodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="198" pageNumber="477" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kofordi">Akodon kofordi Myers &amp; Patton, 1989</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3818814378" pageId="198" pageNumber="477">“Agualani, 9 km N by road Limbani, Depto. Puno, Peru, elevation 2840 m.”</materialsCitation>
This species is monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="198" pageNumber="477" type="distribution">
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6707470" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6707470" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6707470/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="198" pageNumber="477" targetBox="[1446,2038,3061,3475]" targetPageId="198">
<paragraph blockId="198.[2060,2654,3058,3480]" pageId="198" pageNumber="477">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[2061,2237,3211,3244]" pageId="198" pageNumber="477">Distribution.</emphasis>
E Andean slopes from SE Peru to CW Bolivia.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="199" lastPageNumber="478" pageId="198" pageNumber="477" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="198.[2060,2654,3058,3480]" lastBlockId="199.[105,1313,300,763]" lastPageId="199" lastPageNumber="478" pageId="198" pageNumber="477">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[2061,2310,3290,3323]" pageId="198" pageNumber="477">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 96 mm, tail 78 mm, ear 15 mm, hindfoot 22-5 mm. No specific data are available for body weight. Koford’s Grass Mouse is a moderately large species of 
<taxonomicName box="[2393,2492,3451,3480]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Akodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="198" pageNumber="477" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Akodon</taxonomicName>
. Dorsum is dark olivaceous brown; tail is unicolored; and hindfeet are covered with banded hairs. Chromosomal complement is 2n = 40, FN = 40.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="199" pageNumber="478" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="199.[105,1313,300,763]" pageId="199" pageNumber="478">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[107,218,378,407]" pageId="199" pageNumber="478">Habitat.</emphasis>
Elfin forest and 
<taxonomicName box="[473,544,378,407]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Puna" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="199" pageNumber="478" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Puna</taxonomicName>
at elevations of 1800-3700 m. Koford’s Grass Mouse occupies moist bunchgrass, disturbed shrubby areas, and forest including 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hill" authorityYear="1753" box="[1140,1218,418,447]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Alnus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="199" pageNumber="478" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Alnus</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="199" pageNumber="478" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Betulaceae</taxonomicName>
) cloud forest and 
<taxonomicName box="[457,565,453,486]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Polylepis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="199" pageNumber="478" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Polylepis</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[585,716,453,486]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="199" pageNumber="478" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Rosaceae</taxonomicName>
) woodlands.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
